Total Halts Gonfreville Unit After Fire Injured Two, AFP Reports

-- B y   T a r a   P a t e l
-- 
2011-05-10T07:11:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/total-halts-gonfreville-unit-after-fire-injured-two-afp-reports.html
Total SA (FP)  halted a crude-processing
unit at the Gonfreville l’Orcher refinery near Le Havre
yesterday following a fire that injured two workers, AFP
reported, citing an unidentified company official.  The fire started at a distillation unit and was brought
under control within 15 minutes, according to the report.
Halting the unit will have “limited” impact on operations, the
company official was quoted as saying.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Tara Patel in Paris at 
